==English==
===Etymology===
Latin ''[[lethifer]]'', ''[[letifer]]'', from ''[[lethum]]'', ''[[letum]]'', death + ''[[ferre]]'' to bear, to bring: Compare French ''[[léthifère]]''.
===Adjective===
'''lethiferous'''
#{{obsolete}} [[deadly]], [[lethal]]
#:'''1658:''' [[w:John Robinson|John Robinson]], ''Eudoxa'', p. 151 - Those that are really '''lethiferous''' are but excrescencies of sin

